President Cyril Ramaphosa has granted veteran broadcaster, Xolani Gwala, a special provincial official funeral. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -President Cyril Ramaphosa has granted veteran broadcaster, Xolani Gwala, a Special Provincial Official Funeral Category 2. Gwala died a week ago after battling cancer. READ: Seasoned broadcaster Xolani Gwala has died The respected journalist will be buried in his hometown of Impendle in KwaZulu-Natal on Saturday. The announcement from the Presidency means all flags in KZN will be flown at half-mast. Ramaphosa has hailed Gwala as a youthful veteran who embodied values of listening and being open to opposing views.